CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 8, 1952, pg. 1, reads: "TURNOUT OF VOTERS WAS HEAVY - With and unprecedented number of voters turning out for Tuesday's election, scenes like this were repeated many places in Hill District and most other parts of the city and nation on most other parts of the city and nation. This picture was taken in the polling place for the Third District, Third Ward. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of women, and men, including one wearing light colored jacket and dark shirt standing with hands in jacket pockets, and many wearing political ribbons on chest, standing in front of table in Third Ward polling place with brick walls
